---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Project Prep Agent">

  <section class="agent-intro">
    <p class="agent-eyebrow">Agent Guide</p>
    <h1 class="agent-h1">Project Prep</h1>
    <p class="agent-summary">
      The Project Prep agent sets up a new design project before you start designing. It runs
      a structured intake, selects the right competitors for the page type, takes desktop and
      mobile screenshots of their equivalent pages, creates a Figma file with a Brief &amp;
      Requirements page, Competitor Research page, and blank Working canvas — then hands it
      back ready to design. The goal is to eliminate setup overhead entirely.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Setup callout ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <a href="/getting-started" class="setup-callout">
    <span class="setup-callout-icon">⚙</span>
    <div>
      <p class="setup-callout-title">First time? Complete the setup guide first</p>
      <p class="setup-callout-sub">You'll need GitHub Desktop, the Claude Code desktop app, the Chrome extension, and the agent skills installed before any agent will work. →</p>
    </div>
  </a>

  <!-- ── Before you start ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Before you start</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>A rough idea of what you're working on — even a one-line description is enough to start ("redesign the basket", "new mobile nav")</li>
      <li>Figma access: the agent creates and structures a Figma file, so the Figma MCP server must be connected in your Claude Code session</li>
      <li>
        <strong>You'll need to duplicate the Design System template manually first.</strong>
        The Figma MCP can only create blank files — it can't duplicate an existing one. The agent
        will ask you to duplicate the Myprotein Design System template (File → Duplicate) and share
        the URL of your duplicate. This ensures brand styles and variables are already in the file.
        It takes about 10 seconds.
      </li>
      <li>Optional: any constraints or context worth knowing upfront — "mobile-first only", "must use existing components", "targeting the supplement audience"</li>
      <li>Optional: direct URLs to the competitor pages you want screenshotted. If you have them, share them — it's significantly faster than the agent navigating there itself</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── How to trigger ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How to trigger it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">Use the slash command directly, or describe the project you're starting:</p>
    <div class="trigger-block">
      <code class="trigger-command">/myprotein-prep-agent</code>
    </div>
    <div class="trigger-examples">
      <span class="trigger-chip">"prep for the basket redesign"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"set up a Figma file for the checkout"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"I need to redesign the PDP"</span>
      <span class="trigger-chip">"start a new design project for the search page"</span>
    </div>
    <p class="guide-body guide-body--tip">The more context you give up front — page type, goal, constraints — the less the agent needs to ask. A phrase like "prep for the basket redesign, mobile-first, existing component library" will kick off with minimal follow-up questions.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step-by-step walkthrough ───────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-step walkthrough</h2>
    <ol class="steps">
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">1</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Intake — all questions at once</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent asks six questions in a single message — it doesn't drip-feed them one at a
            time. It wants to know: what the task is, what the goal is, any constraints or context,
            which pages to include in the Figma file (brief is always included; competitor research
            and working canvas are optional), which competitors to focus on if any, and whether you
            have direct page URLs to screenshot. Answer what you know and skip anything you don't
            — the agent will make sensible assumptions and note them in the brief.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">2</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Plan is confirmed before work begins</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Based on your answers, the agent summarises exactly what it's about to do — the Figma
            file name, pages it'll create, and the specific competitor pages it'll screenshot — and
            waits for your confirmation before starting. No surprises.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">3</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Competitors are selected from the reference list</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Based on the page type, the agent picks 3–5 competitors from
            <code>references/competitor-brands.md</code> — prioritising brands with proven
            strengths for this specific task. If you specified competitors in the intake, those
            are used first, supplemented if needed. Maximum 5 — more becomes noise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">4</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Competitor screenshots are taken</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            If you provided direct URLs in the intake, the agent goes straight to screenshotting
            — no navigation needed. If not, it navigates to each competitor's equivalent page.
            Each competitor gets a desktop (1440px) and mobile (390px) full-page screenshot, plus
            2–3 written observations about what they do well or differently for this page type.
            Screenshots are saved to <code>/tmp/competitor-screenshots/</code> ready for upload.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">5</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">Figma file is structured</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            Working in your duplicated Design System template, the agent creates three pages.
            <strong>Brief &amp; Requirements</strong> — a clean document with project overview,
            goal, constraints, must/should/nice-to-have requirements derived from your intake,
            and suggested success metrics.
            <strong>Competitor Research</strong> — a labelled section per competitor with desktop
            and mobile frames (1440×900px and 390×844px) loaded with the screenshots from Step 4,
            plus the observations text.
            <strong>Working</strong> — a blank canvas ready for design.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <span class="step-number">6</span>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3 class="step-title">File link is shared back</h3>
          <p class="step-desc">
            The agent sends back the Figma file URL with a summary of what's in it — which
            competitors were researched and which pages are ready. If you're in Claude.ai rather
            than Claude Code, competitor screenshots won't be auto-uploaded; the agent will
            label each frame and tell you which files to drop in manually.
          </p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Tips and common issues ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Tips and common issues</h2>
    <ul class="tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Always duplicate the template yourself first.</strong>
        The Figma MCP <code>create_new_file</code> tool creates a blank file with no brand styles
        or variables. Duplicating the Myprotein Design System template takes 10 seconds and means
        your project file has everything linked from the start — no manual style imports needed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Provide direct competitor URLs when you have them.</strong>
        Basket and cart pages require adding a product before the competitor page is visible —
        which involves navigation, cookie banners, and potential bot detection. Providing the
        direct URL skips all of this and makes the screenshotting significantly faster and more
        reliable.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Competitor page is blocked or inaccessible.</strong>
        If a domain is blocked by the browser tool, the agent creates a placeholder frame with
        written observations based on its knowledge of the site. It will note which frames need
        to be filled manually. This still gives you the Figma structure and the brief — just
        without the screenshot for that one brand.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Keep competitors to five or fewer.</strong>
        More than five competitors on a research page becomes overwhelming to work from. If you
        have a long list, the agent will pick the most relevant based on the page type. You can
        always run the agent again later for a second pass.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The brief derives requirements from what you tell it.</strong>
        If you give it very little in the intake, the brief will be generic. The more specific
        you are about the goal and constraints, the more useful the must/should/nice-to-have
        breakdown will be as a working reference during design.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .setup-callout {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    background: #EEF6F7;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 57, 66, 0.18);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .setup-callout:hover { background: #E4F0F2; }
  .setup-callout-icon { font-size: 18px; color: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.6; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }
  .setup-callout-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .setup-callout-sub { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--color-text-body); }

  .agent-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .agent-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .agent-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .agent-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .guide-section { margin-bottom: 52px; }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .sub-heading {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin: 20px 0 8px;
  }

  .guide-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-body--tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .checklist {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .checklist li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 22px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .checklist li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .trigger-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .trigger-command {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    padding: 8px 18px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .trigger-examples {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .trigger-chip {
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-chip);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .code-block {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .file-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .file-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    padding-left: 16px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .file-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .steps { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 34px;
    height: 34px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .step-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .tips-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .tips-list li {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .tips-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
</style>
